com.nokia.dempsy.router
Interface RoutingStrategy

public interface RoutingStrategy

A RoutingStrategy is responsible for determining how to find the appropriate Node within a given cluster given a MessageKey. It has both an RoutingStrategy.Inbound side and an RoutingStrategy.Outbound side that work together using the MpCluster to do the bookkeeping necessary.

A simple example would be: a non-elastic, fixed-width cluster RoutingStrategy that simply selects the Node to send a message to based on the mod ('%' operator) of the hash of a message's key with the number of nodes in the cluster.

In this example the RoutingStrategy.Inbound strategy, which would be instantiated in each node, would be implemented to register the its current Node with the MpCluster. The RoutingStrategy.Outbound side would use the registered information to select the appropriate Node.

As mentioned, RoutingStrategy implementations need to be balanced. The RoutingStrategy.Inbound can safely assume that the RoutingStrategy.Outbound created from the same strategy was responsible for setting up the cluster.

RoutingStrategy.Inbound and RoutingStrategy.Outbound need to be thought of in terms of the stages of a pipeline in a Dempsy application. E.g.: 

 
 Adaptor --> inbound1|Stage1|outbound2 --> inbound2|Stage2|outbound3 ...

Notice that outbound2 and inbound2 require coordination and are therefore defined in the ApplicationDefinition using a single RoutingStrategy as part of the ClusterDefinition that defines Stage2

As an example, the DecentralizedRoutingStrategy's Inbound and Outbound coordinate through the cluster. The Inbound side negotiates for slot ownership and those slots contain enough information for the Outbound side

Implementations must be able to handle multi-threaded access.

Method Detail

createInbound

RoutingStrategy.Inbound createInbound(ClusterInfoSession cluster,
                                      ClusterId clusterId,
                                      Collection<Class<?>> messageTypes,
                                      Destination thisDestination,
                                      RoutingStrategy.Inbound.KeyspaceResponsibilityChangeListener listener)
This method will be called from the Dempsy framework in order to instantiate the one Inbound for 'this' node. Keep in mind that when running in LocalVm mode there can be more than one inbound per process.

Parameters:
cluster - is the cluster information manager handle for 'this' node.
messageTypes - is the types of messages that Dempsy determined could be handled by the MessageProcessor in this node. This information should be shared across to the RoutingStrategy.Outbound and registered with the RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator to allow Dempsy to restrict messages to the appropriate types.
thisDestination - is the transport Destination instance that represents how to communicate with 'this' node.
Returns:
the RoutingStrategy.Inbound instance.

createOutbound

RoutingStrategy.Outbound createOutbound(RoutingStrategy.Outbound.Coordinator coordinator,
                                        ClusterInfoSession cluster,
                                        ClusterId clusterId)
The RoutingStrategy needs to create an RoutingStrategy.Outbound that corresponds to the given cluster. It should do this in a manner that absolutely succeeds even if the cluster information manager is in a bad state. This is why this method takes stable parameters and throws no exception.

Parameters:
coordinator - is the coordinator that the newly created RoutingStrategy.Outbound can use to call back on the framework.
clusterId - is the cluster id that the RoutingStrategy.Outbound is being created for.
Returns:
a new RoutingStrategy.Outbound that manages the selection of a Destination given a message destined for the given cluster.
